<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870616-0008 </DOCNO><HL> Ford Unit ReceivesArmy Computer JobTotaling $50.4 Million</HL><DD> 06/16/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> F UTX GM GMH UIS ETN GQ LK GE WXDEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ford Aerospace andamp; Communications Corp., a unit of Ford Motor Co., received a $50.4 million Army contract for computer equipment.    Sikorsky Aircraft, a unit of United Technologies Corp., won Navy contracts totaling $37.7 million for SH-60B helicopter production and a helicopter test program.    Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp., was awarded contracts totaling $28.8 million for TOW missile equipment for the Army and Phoenix missile studies for the Navy.    Unisys Corp. was given a $27.6 million Navy contract for shipboard weapon fire control systems.    Eaton Corp. was issued a $22.2 million Navy contract for EA-6B aircraft equipment.    Grumman Corp. got a $19.1 million Navy contract for spare parts for E-2C aircraft radars.    Lockheed Corp. units received Navy contracts totaling $12.8 million for EA-6B aircraft equipment and P-3 aircraft production.    General Electric Co. won a $12.3 million Navy contract for P-3 aircraft equipment.    Lear Siegler Inc. was issued Navy contracts totaling $11.8 million for improvements in aircraft electronic equipment.    Westinghouse Electric Corp. was given Air Force contracts totaling $10.7 million for equipment for F-16 aircraft radars.    Electro-Space Systems Inc. won contracts totaling $10.3 million for communications equipment for the Air Force and the Army. </TEXT></DOC>